  "discrete": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Discrete",
    "subtitle": "Variation Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "The Variation only grants the specific abilities of its current Magnitude rating, and does not grant lower-Magnitude benefits. It can often be bought multiple times at different ratings to access those further capabilities.",
      "Most Discrete Variations cannot have their Magnitude temporarily increased or decreased by Adaptations or Scars. Exceptions to this will be noted in the Variation's description â€” however, in such a case, {{NAME}} must determine how the Variation functions at <em>every</em> available Magnitude at the time of purchase.",
      "Scars that would reduce the Magnitude of an active Discrete Variation instead cause the Variation to deactivate after a number of failed Scar Resistance rolls equal to the Variation's Magnitude."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
  "overt": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Overt",
    "subtitle": "Advantage Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "The use of this Advantage is particularly blatant or obvious. Usage increases the likelihood of a conspiracy noting your activity. It may also trigger breaking points in Baselines, particularly if the Advantage is supernatural.",
      "At the Storyteller's discretion, Overt Advantages used in seclusion (out of sight of witnesses and out of reach of mundane surveillance) may not attract additional conspiracy attention."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
  "perpetual": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Perpetual",
    "subtitle": "Variation Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "If this Variation is Persistent:",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>It is always active.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>If Overt, it attracts conspiracy attention even if {{NAME}} didn't derive a benefit from it during the chapter.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>{{NAME}} gains a +5 bonus on any Clash of Wills rolls involving the Variation.</span>",
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
  "reflexive": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Reflexive",
    "subtitle": "Variation Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "This Variation can be activated with a reflexive action, rather than an instant action."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
  "subtle": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Subtle",
    "subtitle": "Advantage Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "The use of this Variation is easy to conceal. Using it does not increase the likelihood of a conspiracy noticing {{NAME}}'s activity."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
  "tiered": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Tiered",
    "subtitle": "Variation Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "This Variation grants {{NAME}} all of its listed benefits up to the Variation's current Magnitude.{{BR}}In some cases, activating the Variation grants all of these abilities at once; in others, each effect requires a separate activation."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
  "toggled": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Toggled",
    "subtitle": "Variation Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "If this Variation is Persistent: \
      <ul> \
        <li>It is only active when {{NAME}} chooses to activate it, which requires an instant action (unless this Variation is also Reflexive).</li> \
        <li>Once activated, it remains active until the end of the scene.</li> \
      </ul>"
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
  "secondary": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Secondary",
    "subtitle": "Scar Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "This Scar takes the type (mental, physical, or social) of its secondary Scar."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 111
    }
  },
  "directedOnly": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Directed-Only",
    "subtitle": "Scar/Deviation Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "This Scar or Deviation may only entangle Variations with the 'Directed' keyword."
    ],
    "source": {
